AttachPlugin.document: This API is used to bind a plugin to an API.
AttachPlugin.name: Binds a plugin to an API

BindApiApp.document: This API is used to bind an application to an API.
BindApiApp.name: Binds application to API

BindEnvironment.document:
This API is used to bind a usage plan to a service or API.
After you publish a service to an environment, if the API requires authentication and can be called only when it is bound to a usage plan, you can use this API to bind a usage plan to the specified environment.
Currently, a usage plan can be bound to an API; however, under the same service, usage plans bound to a service and usage plans bound to an API cannot coexist. Therefore, in an environment to which a service-level usage plan has already been bound, please use the `DemoteServiceUsagePlan` API to degrade it.
BindEnvironment.name: Binds usage plan to service or API

BindIPStrategy.document: This API is used to bind an IP policy to an API.
BindIPStrategy.name: Binds IP policy to API

BindSecretIds.document:
This API is used to bind a key to a usage plan.
You can bind a key to a usage plan and bind the usage plan to an environment where a service is published, so that callers can use the key to call APIs in the service. You can use this API to bind a key to a usage plan.
BindSecretIds.name: Binds key to usage plan

BindSubDomain.document:
This API is used to bind a custom domain name to a service.
Each service in API Gateway provides a default domain name for users to call. If you want to use your own domain name, you can bind a custom domain name to the target service. After getting the ICP filing and configuring the CNAME record between the custom and default domain names, you can directly call the custom domain name.
BindSubDomain.name: Binds custom domain name to service

BuildAPIDoc.document: This API is used to build an API document.
BuildAPIDoc.name: Builds API document

CreateAPIDoc.document: This API is used to create an API document.
CreateAPIDoc.name: Creates API document

CreateApi.document: This API is used to create an API. Before creating an API, you need to create a service, as each API belongs to a certain service.
CreateApi.name: Creates API

CreateApiApp.document: This API is used to create an application.
CreateApiApp.name: Creates application

CreateApiKey.document: This API is used to create an API key pair.
CreateApiKey.name: Creates key

CreateIPStrategy.document: This API is used to create a service IP policy.
CreateIPStrategy.name: Creates service IP policy

CreatePlugin.document: This API is used to create an API Gateway plugin.
CreatePlugin.name: Creates a plugin

CreateService.document:
This API is used to create a service.
A service is the biggest usage unit in API Gateway. Each service can contain multiple APIs and one default domain name for invocation. You can also bind your own custom domain name to a service.
CreateService.name: Creates service

CreateUpstream.document: This API is used to create an upstream.
CreateUpstream.name: Creates an upstream

CreateUsagePlan.document:
This API is used to create a usage plan.
To use API Gateway, you need to create a usage plan and bind it to a service environment.
CreateUsagePlan.name: Creates usage plan

DeleteAPIDoc.document: This API is used to delete an API document.
DeleteAPIDoc.name: Deletes API document

DeleteApi.document: This API is used to delete a created API.
DeleteApi.name: Deletes API

DeleteApiApp.document: This API is used to delete a created application.
DeleteApiApp.name: Deletes application

DeleteApiKey.document: This API is used to delete an API key pair.
DeleteApiKey.name: Deletes key

DeleteIPStrategy.document: This API is used to delete a service IP policy.
DeleteIPStrategy.name: Deletes service IP policy

DeletePlugin.document: This API is used to delete an API Gateway plugin.
DeletePlugin.name: Deletes a plugin

DeleteService.document: This API is used to delete a service in API Gateway.
DeleteService.name: Deletes service

DeleteServiceSubDomainMapping.document:
This API is used to delete a custom domain name mapping in a service environment.
You can use this API if you use a custom domain name and custom mapping. Please note that if you delete all mappings in all environments, a failure will be returned when this API is called.
DeleteServiceSubDomainMapping.name: Deletes the path mapping of custom domain name

DeleteUpstream.document: This API is used to delete an upstream. Note that you can only delete an upstream when it’s not bound with any APIs.
DeleteUpstream.name: Deletes an upstream

DeleteUsagePlan.document: This API is used to delete a usage plan.
DeleteUsagePlan.name: Deletes a usage plan

DemoteServiceUsagePlan.document:
This API is used to degrade a usage plan of a service in an environment to the API level.
This operation will be denied if there are no APIs under the service.
This operation will also be denied if the current environment has not been published.
DemoteServiceUsagePlan.name: Demotes usage plan at service level

DescribeAPIDocDetail.document: This API is used to query the details of an API document.
DescribeAPIDocDetail.name: Queries the details of API document

DescribeAPIDocs.document: This API is used to query the list of API documents.
DescribeAPIDocs.name: Queries the list of API documents

DescribeAllPluginApis.document: This API is used to list all APIs that can use this plugin, no matter whether the API is bound with the plugin.
DescribeAllPluginApis.name: Lists all APIs that can use this plugin

DescribeApi.document: This API (`DescribeApi`) is used to query the details of the APIs users manage via Tencent Cloud API Gateway.
DescribeApi.name: Queries API details

DescribeApiApp.document: This API is used to search for an application by application ID.
DescribeApiApp.name: Searches for application

DescribeApiAppBindApisStatus.document: This API is used to query the list of APIs bound to an application.
DescribeApiAppBindApisStatus.name: Queries the list of APIs bound to application

DescribeApiAppsStatus.document: This API is used to query the application list.
DescribeApiAppsStatus.name: Queries application list

DescribeApiBindApiAppsStatus.document: This API is used to query the list of applications bound to an API.
DescribeApiBindApiAppsStatus.name: Queries the list of applications bound to API

DescribeApiEnvironmentStrategy.document: This API is used to display the throttling policies bound to an API.
DescribeApiEnvironmentStrategy.name: Displays throttling policies bound to API

DescribeApiForApiApp.document: This API is used to query the details of an API deployed at API Gateway.
DescribeApiForApiApp.name: Queries API details

DescribeApiKey.document:
This API is used to query the details of a key.
After creating an API key, you can query its details by using this API.
DescribeApiKey.name: Queries key details

DescribeApiKeysStatus.document: This API is used to query the information of one or more API keys.
DescribeApiKeysStatus.name: Queries key list

DescribeApiUsagePlan.document:
This API is used to query the details of API usage plans in a service.
To make authentication and throttling for a service take effect, you need to bind a usage plan to it. This API is used to query all usage plans bound to a service and APIs under it.
DescribeApiUsagePlan.name: Queries the details of API usage plans

DescribeApisStatus.document: This API is used to view a certain API or the list of all APIs under a service and relevant information.
DescribeApisStatus.name: Queries API list

DescribeIPStrategy.document: This API is used to query IP policy details.
DescribeIPStrategy.name: Queries IP policy details

DescribeIPStrategyApisStatus.document: This API is used to query the list of APIs to which an IP policy can be bound, i.e., the difference set between all APIs under the service and the APIs already bound to the policy.
DescribeIPStrategyApisStatus.name: Queries the list of APIs bound to IP policy

DescribeIPStrategysStatus.document: This API is used to query the list of service IP policies.
DescribeIPStrategysStatus.name: Queries service IP policy list

DescribeLogSearch.document: This API is used to search for logs.
DescribeLogSearch.name: Searches for logs

DescribePlugin.document: This API is used to query the plugin details by plugin ID.
DescribePlugin.name: Queries details of a plugin

DescribePluginApis.document: This API is used to query APIs bound with a specified plugin.
DescribePluginApis.name: Queries APIs bound with a plugin

DescribePluginsByApi.document: This API is used to query all plug-ins bound with the API.
DescribePluginsByApi.name: Queries all plug-ins bound with the API.

DescribeService.document: This API is used to query the details of a service, such as its description, domain name, protocol, creation time, and releases.
DescribeService.name: Queries service details

DescribeServiceEnvironmentList.document: This API is used to query the list of environments under a service. All environments and their statuses under the queried service will be returned.
DescribeServiceEnvironmentList.name: Queries service environment list

DescribeServiceEnvironmentReleaseHistory.document:
This API is used to query the release history in a service environment.
A service can only be used when it is published to an environment after creation. This API is used to query the release history in an environment under a service.
DescribeServiceEnvironmentReleaseHistory.name: Queries release history in service environment

DescribeServiceEnvironmentStrategy.document: This API is used to display a service throttling policy.
DescribeServiceEnvironmentStrategy.name: Displays service throttling policy

DescribeServiceForApiApp.document: This API is used to query the details of a service, such as its description, domain name, and protocol.
DescribeServiceForApiApp.name: Queries service details

DescribeServiceReleaseVersion.document:
This API is used to query the list of all published versions under a service.
A service is generally published on several versions. This API can be used to query the published versions.
DescribeServiceReleaseVersion.name: Queries the published versions of service

DescribeServiceSubDomainMappings.document:
This API is used to query the path mappings of a custom domain name.
In API Gateway, you can bind a custom domain name to a service and map its paths. You can customize different path mappings to up to 3 environments under the service. This API is used to query the list of path mappings of a custom domain name bound to a service.
DescribeServiceSubDomainMappings.name: Queries the path mappings of custom domain name

DescribeServiceSubDomains.document:
This API is used to query the list of custom domain names.
In API Gateway, you can bind custom domain names to a service for service call. This API is used to query the list of custom domain names bound to a service.
DescribeServiceSubDomains.name: Queries custom domain name list

DescribeServiceUsagePlan.document:
This API is used to query the details of usage plans in a service.
To make authentication and throttling for a service take effect, you need to bind a usage plan to it. This API is used to query all usage plans bound to a service.
DescribeServiceUsagePlan.name: Queries the usage plan details of service

DescribeServicesStatus.document: This API is used to query the list of one or more services and return relevant domain name, time, and other information.
DescribeServicesStatus.name: Queries service status

DescribeUpstreamBindApis.document: This API is used to query APIs bound with an upstream.
DescribeUpstreamBindApis.name: Queries APIs bound with an upstream

DescribeUpstreams.document: This API is used to query details of upstreams under the current account.
DescribeUpstreams.name: Queries details of upstreams under the current account

DescribeUsagePlan.document: This API is used to query the details of a usage plan, such as its name, QPS, creation time, and bound environment.
DescribeUsagePlan.name: Queries usage plan details

DescribeUsagePlanEnvironments.document:
This API is used to query the list of environments bound to a usage plan.
After binding a usage plan to environments, you can use this API to query all service environments bound to the usage plan.
DescribeUsagePlanEnvironments.name: Queries the list of environments bound to usage plan

DescribeUsagePlanSecretIds.document:
This API is used to query the list of keys bound to a usage plan.
In API Gateway, a usage plan can be bound to multiple key pairs. You can use this API to query the list of keys bound to it.
DescribeUsagePlanSecretIds.name: Queries the list of keys bound to usage plan

DescribeUsagePlansStatus.document: This API is used to query the list of usage plans.
DescribeUsagePlansStatus.name: Queries usage plan list

DetachPlugin.document: This API is used to unbind an API from the plugin.
DetachPlugin.name: Unbinds an API from a plugin

DisableApiKey.document: This API is used to disable an API key.
DisableApiKey.name: Disables key

EnableApiKey.document: This API is used to enable a disabled API key.
EnableApiKey.name: Enables key

GenerateApiDocument.document: This API is used to automatically generate API documents and SDKs. One document and one SDK will be generated for each environment under each service, respectively.
GenerateApiDocument.name: Generates documents and SDKs

ImportOpenApi.document: This API is used to import an OpenAPI to API gateway.
ImportOpenApi.name: Imports OpenAPI

ModifyAPIDoc.document: This API is used to modify an API document.
ModifyAPIDoc.name: Modifies API document

ModifyApi.document: This API is used to modify an API. You can call this API to edit/modify a configured API. The modified API takes effect only after its service is published to the corresponding environment again.
ModifyApi.name: Modifies API

ModifyApiApp.document: This API is used to modify a created API.
ModifyApiApp.name: Modifies application

ModifyApiEnvironmentStrategy.document: This API is used to modify an API throttling policy.
ModifyApiEnvironmentStrategy.name: Modifies API throttling policy

ModifyApiIncrement.document: This API is used to incrementally update an API and mainly called by programs (different from `ModifyApi`, which requires that full API parameters be passed in and is suitable for use in the console).
ModifyApiIncrement.name: Updates API incrementally

ModifyIPStrategy.document: This API is used to modify a service IP policy.
ModifyIPStrategy.name: Modifies service IP policy

ModifyPlugin.document: This API is used to modify a plugin.
ModifyPlugin.name: Modifies a plugin

ModifyService.document: This API is used to modify the relevant information of a service. After a service is created, its name, description, and service type can be modified.
ModifyService.name: Modifies service

ModifyServiceEnvironmentStrategy.document: This API is used to modify a service throttling policy.
ModifyServiceEnvironmentStrategy.name: Modifies service throttling policy

ModifySubDomain.document: This API is used to modify the path mapping in the custom domain name settings of a service. The path mapping rule can be modified before it is bound to the custom domain name.
ModifySubDomain.name: Modifies the custom domain name of service

ModifyUpstream.document: This API is used to modify an upstream.
ModifyUpstream.name: Modifies an upstream

ModifyUsagePlan.document: This API is used to modify the name, description, and QPS of a usage plan.
ModifyUsagePlan.name: Modifies usage plan

ReleaseService.document:
This API is used to publish a service.
An API Gateway service can only be called when it is published to an environment and takes effect after creation. This API is used to publish a service to an environment such as the `release` environment.
ReleaseService.name: Publishes service

ResetAPIDocPassword.document: This API is used to reset the password of an API document.
ResetAPIDocPassword.name: Resets the password of API document

UnBindEnvironment.document: This API is used to unbind a usage plan from a specified environment.
UnBindEnvironment.name: Unbinds usage plan from service environment

UnBindIPStrategy.document: This API is used to unbind an IP policy from a service.
UnBindIPStrategy.name: Unbinds IP policy from service

UnBindSecretIds.document: This API is used to unbind a key from a usage plan.
UnBindSecretIds.name: Unbinds key from usage plan

UnBindSubDomain.document:
This API is used to unbind a custom domain name.
After binding a custom domain name to a service by using API Gateway, you can use this API to unbind it.
UnBindSubDomain.name: Unbinds custom domain name from service

UnReleaseService.document:
This API is used to deactivate a service.
Only after a service is published to an environment can its APIs be called. You can call this API to deactivate a service in the release environment. Once deactivated, the service cannot be called.
UnReleaseService.name: Deactivates service

UnbindApiApp.document: This API is used to unbind an application from an API.
UnbindApiApp.name: Unbinds application from API

UpdateApiAppKey.document: This API is used to update an application key.
UpdateApiAppKey.name: Updates an application key

UpdateApiKey.document: This API is used to update a created API key pair.
UpdateApiKey.name: Updates key

UpdateService.document: This API is used to switch the running version of a service published in an environment to a specified version. After you create a service by using API Gateway and publish it to an environment, multiple versions will be generated during development. In this case, you can call this API to switch versions.
UpdateService.name: Updates service version

members.document:
The returned result contains any number of logs, which are in the following format:
'[$app_id][$env_name][$service_id][$http_host][$api_id][$uri][$scheme][rsp_st:$status][ups_st:$upstream_status]'
'[cip:$remote_addr][uip:$upstream_addr][vip:$server_addr][rsp_len:$bytes_sent][req_len:$request_length]'
'[req_t:$request_time][ups_rsp_t:$upstream_response_time][ups_conn_t:$upstream_connect_time][ups_head_t:$upstream_header_time]’
'[err_msg:$err_msg][tcp_rtt:$tcpinfo_rtt][$pid][$time_local][req_id:$request_id]';

Note:
app_id: user ID.
env_name: environment name.
service_id: service ID.
http_host: domain name.
api_id: API ID.
uri: request path.
scheme: HTTP/HTTPS protocol.
rsp_st: request response status code.
ups_st: backend business server response status code (if the request is passed through to the backend, this variable will not be empty. If the request is blocked in API Gateway, this variable will be displayed as `-`).
cip: client IP.
uip: backend business service (upstream) IP.
vip: VIP requested to be accessed.
rsp_len: response length.
req_len: request length.
req_t: total request response time.
ups_rsp_t: total backend response time (time between connection establishment by API Gateway and backend response receipt).
ups_conn_t: time when the backend business server is successfully connected to.
ups_head_t: time when the backend response header arrives.
err_msg: error message.
tcp_rtt: client TCP connection information. RTT (Round Trip Time) consists of three parts: link propagation delay, end system processing delay, and queuing delay in router cache.
req_id: request ID.
